<h2>The HTML &lt;meta&gt; Element</h2>
<p>The <code class="w3-codespan">&lt;meta&gt;</code> element is used to specify which character set 
is used, page description, keywords, 
author, and other metadata.</p>
<p>Metadata is used by browsers (how to display content), 
by search engines (keywords), and other web services.</p>

<p>Define the character set used:</p>
<div class="w3-example">
<div class="w3-code notranslate htmlHigh">
&lt;meta charset=&quot;UTF-8&quot;&gt;</div>
</div>

<p>Define a description of your web page:</p>
<div class="w3-example">
<div class="w3-code notranslate htmlHigh">
&lt;meta name=&quot;description&quot; content=&quot;Free Web tutorials&quot;&gt;</div>
</div>

<p>Define keywords for search engines:</p>
<div class="w3-example">
<div class="w3-code notranslate htmlHigh">
&lt;meta name=&quot;keywords&quot; content=&quot;HTML, CSS, XML, JavaScript&quot;&gt;</div>
</div>

<p>Define the author of a page:</p>
<div class="w3-example">
<div class="w3-code notranslate htmlHigh">
&lt;meta name=&quot;author&quot; content=&quot;John Doe&quot;&gt;</div>
</div>

<p>Refresh document every 30 seconds:</p>
<div class="w3-example">
<div class="w3-code notranslate htmlHigh">
&lt;meta http-equiv=&quot;refresh&quot; content=&quot;30&quot;&gt;</div>
</div>

<p>Example of <code class="w3-codespan">&lt;meta&gt;</code> tags:</p>
<div class="w3-example">
<h3>Example</h3>
<div class="w3-code notranslate htmlHigh">
 &lt;meta charset=&quot;UTF-8&quot;&gt;<br>&lt;meta name=&quot;description&quot; content=&quot;Free Web tutorials&quot;&gt;<br>&lt;meta name=&quot;keywords&quot; content=&quot;HTML,CSS,XML,JavaScript&quot;&gt;<br>&lt;meta name=&quot;author&quot; content=&quot;John 
  Doe&quot;&gt;<br></div>
