<h2>The HTML &lt;script&gt; Element</h2>
<p>The <code class="w3-codespan">&lt;script&gt;</code> element is used to define client-side JavaScripts.</p>
<p>This JavaScript writes &quot;Hello JavaScript!&quot; into an HTML element with id=&quot;demo&quot;:</p>

<div class="w3-example">
<h3>Example</h3>
<div class="w3-code notranslate htmlHigh">
&lt;script&gt;<br>function myFunction {<br>
 &#xA0;&#xA0;&#xA0;
 document.getElementById(&quot;demo&quot;).innerHTML = &quot;Hello JavaScript!&quot;;<br>
 }<br>&lt;/script&gt;</div>
<a class="w3-btn w3-margin-bottom" href="tryit?filename=tryhtml_head_script" target="_blank">Try it Yourself &#xBB;</a>
