<h2>The HTML &lt;base&gt; Element</h2>
<p>The <code class="w3-codespan">&lt;base&gt;</code> element specifies the base URL and base target for all relative URLs in a page:</p>
<div class="w3-example">
<h3>Example</h3>
 <div class="w3-code notranslate htmlHigh">
  &lt;base href=&quot;https://www.w3schools.com/images/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;<br>
</div>
<a class="w3-btn w3-margin-bottom" href="tryit?filename=tryhtml_head_base" target="_blank">Try it Yourself &#xBB;</a>
</div>
<hr>

<h2>Omitting &lt;html&gt;, &lt;head&gt; and &lt;body&gt;?</h2>
<p>According to the HTML5 standard; the <code class="w3-codespan">&lt;html&gt;</code>, the <code class="w3-codespan">&lt;body&gt;</code>, and the <code class="w3-codespan">&lt;head&gt;</code> tag can 
be omitted.</p>
<p>The following code will validate as HTML5:</p>
<div class="w3-example">
<h3>Example</h3>
<div class="w3-code notranslate htmlHigh">
    &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;<br>&lt;title&gt;Page Title&lt;/title&gt;<br>
    <br>
 &lt;h1&gt;This is a heading&lt;/h1&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;</div>
<a class="w3-btn w3-margin-bottom" href="tryit?filename=tryhtml_head_none" target="_blank">Try it Yourself &#xBB;</a>
</div>
<div class="w3-panel w3-note">
  <p><strong>Note:</strong></p>
  <p>W3Schools does not recommend omitting the <code class="w3-codespan">&lt;html&gt;</code> and <code class="w3-codespan">&lt;body&gt;</code> 
  tags. Omitting these tags can crash DOM or XML software and produce errors in older browsers 
  (IE9).</p>
  <p>However, omitting the <code class="w3-codespan">&lt;head&gt;</code> tag has been a common practice for quite some 
  time now.</p>
</div>
